\par }\pard \s15\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f1\fs22 Lesson        10 b               }{\b\f1\fs22\ul Nama }{\f1\fs22\ul  }{\b\f1\fs22\ul Sankirtana \endash  Yuga Dharma}{\f1\fs22                           xx min
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs22 
\par Introduce session:
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs22 Facilitator to introduce students to the concept of Yuga and Yuga Dharma.  Co-facilitator to distribute handouts to the students.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs22 
\par Group Work:}{\f1\fs22 
\par 
\par Students to go through the handout/worksheet and fill in the appropriate answers.
\par 
\par Facilitator asks for answers from the students, puts on the black board and summarizes.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs22 Short Lecture:}{\f1\fs22 
\par 
\par Facilitator to speak on the meaning of Hare Krishna maha mantra.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs22 Group Work:
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs22 Groups of 3 work on a handout containing a paragraph on the benefits of chanting.
\par 
\par Groups discuss, list and prioratises the benefits of chanting.
\par 
\par Facilitator guides the discussion, co-facilitator notes on the black board.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs22 Handouts:
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs22 Co-facilitator distributes handouts containing slokas from Bhagavad Gita.  Facilitator introduces the task of identifying the various key words which refer to chanting.
\par 
\par Facilitator encourages the students to agree to chant 1 mala per day.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs22 Group Work:}{\f1\fs22 
\par 
\par Facilitator explains the task of observing the co-facilitator chanting the Hare Krishna maha mantra the right way and note down their observations in the work sheets provided to them.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs22 Group Work:}{\f1\fs22 
\par 
\par Co-facilitator explains the task of observing the facilitator chanting the Hare Krishna maha mantra the wrong way and note down their observations in the work sheets already provided to them.
\par 
\par Facilitator asks for responses from the groups about the guidelines for chanting the right way and wrong way.  Co-facilitator lists it on the black board.  
\par 
\par As facilitator summarizes the topic, co-facilitator distributes handouts for the next task.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs22 Group Work:}{\f1\fs22 
\par 
\par Students identify both the right way and wrong way of chanting by circling green (acceptable way) or red (wrong way).
\par 
\par While  facilitator leads the discussion driving home the various do\rquote s and dont\rquote s of chanting, co-facilitator distributes a handout listing the various do\rquote s and don\rquote t\rquote s.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs22 Role Play:}{\f1\fs22 
\par 
\par Facilitator calls for 2 volunteers to convince co-facilitator playing the role of a friend of the volunteers to take up to chanting.
\par 
\par Facilitator leads the discussion on the effectiveness of the preaching of the two volunteers.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs22 Round Up:
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs22 Facilitator focuses the attention of the class to their promise to chant daily.
